content.description:
Unicorns and Rainbows 5.10a ** (45') F(3b)

Belay on the grassy ramp at the far left end of the face and climb the slab and the middle headwall to the pair of chains directly above. Very short but with a very sweet series of moves getting past the 2nd bolt.
content.location: Far left end of the face.

content.description:
Trigger Warning - 5.5 * 60' F(5b)

Climbs the right side of the slab to traverse left below the final headwall to below the 2 chain anchors. Clip one of the chain hangers to protect the final (crux) move.
content.protection: Fixed - 5 bolts to the shared chain anchors.
content.location: Right most of the three routes on the grey slab

content.description:
Everyone A Karen - 5.7** (60') F(5b)

Left most route to the set of chains on the right side of the SW Face slab. Clip one of the chain hangers to protect the final move.
content.location: Begin about 10' left of the middle route ("Ok Boomer") and climb to the shared anchors on the right.

content.description:
Black Lines Matter 5.8 ** (55') F (4b)

Begin 5' left of Everyone a Karen; mounting the initial headwall (1st crux) then climb the slab to the steep arete at the right edge of the left middle headwall. Shares chain anchors with All Routes Matter

All Routes Matter 5.7 ** (55') F (4b)

Climbs the middle of the middle headwall, a little inconsistent but with a great (short) middle section, chain anchors on top.
content.location: Begin at the left end of the lower face, climb the lower headwall to the slab and then climb the middle of the middle headwall.

content.description:
Ok Boomer - 5.6 ** (55') F(5b)

The middle route up the grey slab with the short headwalls at the bottom and top. Clip one of the chain hangers to protect the final move.
content.location: Middle route directly below the 2 chain anchors on the right, begins about 10' left of Trigger Warning
